sage.physics

Interface IPhysicsObject

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    JBulletBoxObject, JBulletCapsuleObject, JBulletCapsuleXObject, JBulletCapsuleZObject, JBulletConeObject, JBulletConeXObject, JBulletConeZObject, JBulletCylinderObject, JBulletCylinderXObject, JBulletCylinderZObject, JBulletPhysicsObject, JBulletSphereObject, JBulletStaticPlaneObject, ODE4JBoxObject, ODE4JCapsuleObject, ODE4JCapsuleXObject, ODE4JCapsuleZObject, ODE4JCylinderObject, ODE4JCylinderXObject, ODE4JCylinderZObject, ODE4JPhysicsObject, ODE4JSphereObject, ODE4JStaticPlaneObject

    public interface IPhysicsObject
    This interface defines the attributes of an arbitrary object in the physics world simulation.
    Author:
    Russell Bolles, John Clevenger

      • isDynamic

        boolean isDynamic()
        Returns a flag indicating whether this IPhysicsObject is dynamic or static. Dynamic objects have mass and participate in physics solutions such as collisions.
        Returns:
        Whether this object is dynamic or not

      • setSleepThresholds

        void setSleepThresholds(float linearThreshold,
                        float angularThreshold)
        Sets the sleep threshold for this physics object. The sleep threshold determines at what velocity an object is determined to have come to rest and thus is no longer updated by the physics engine until another object or force affects the object. This can slightly improve performance and help with object having a slight vibrating effect when they should come to rest.
        Parameters:
        linearThreshold -
        angularThreshold -

        angularDamping -
